
Objective

Practice recovering from mistakes.

Requirements

1. Make a commit with a typo
2. Amend the commit to fix the typo
3. Accidentally delete a file and restore it
4. Unstage a file without losing changes
5. Reset to a previous state

Solution

```bash
# Setup
mkdir undo-practice && cd undo-practice
git init
echo "Important data" > data.txt
git add data.txt
git commit -m "Intial commit"  # Typo!

# 1. Amend commit
git commit --amend -m "Initial commit"

# 2. Delete and restore
rm data.txt
git status  # Shows deleted
git checkout -- data.txt  # Restore

# 3. Unstage a file
echo "More data" > data2.txt
git add data2.txt
git reset HEAD data2.txt  # Unstage
git status  # Shows as untracked

# 4. Reset to previous
echo "Temporary change" >> data.txt
git add data.txt
git reset --hard HEAD  # Discard all changes